For sale is an Armalite National Match AR 15. This is an older version with the WYLDE chamber. I purchased this Armalite from a gentleman several years ago who was a competitive shooter who had used this as his back-up rifle when he shot at the Camp Perry finals. According to him the rifle has had a total of 112 rounds fired through it. The barrel was broken in according to competition standards by cleaning the barrel after each shot for the first 10 rounds and then every 10th round thereafter. this one has a 20" heavy stainless barrel, target sights and is in new condition. There isn't a scratch on it. I have never fired it and it has been in my gun safe for the last several years.
I don't have to sell it but I have other projects to complete. This furniture on this one is Green. 

The factory description of this rifle is below.

Armalite M-15 A2 National Match Rifle

Description;

The Armalite M-15 A2 National Match Rifle is a semi-automatic rifle chambered in .223 Rem. or 5.56 NATO. It has a .223 WYLDE chamber. The M-15 A2 National Match Rifle is a variant of one of four rifles manufactured and sold by Armalite. Armalite recommends the gun for military shooting.

The M-15 A2 National Match Rifle features a National Match rear sight that does not exist on the M-15 A2 Service Model Rifle. The rear sight is adjustable .25 inches for windage and .5 inches for elevation. The gun also features a steel, chrome-lined barrel threaded for a flash suppressor, which reduces the visible signature of the burning gases
 that exit the muzzle. The M-15 A2 National Match Rifle has a two-stage trigger and aluminum-made upper and lower receiver. The first stage of the trigger pull checks in at
 3.5 lbs, the second stage is approximately 4.5 to 5 lbs. 

The M-15 A2 National Match Rifle has a synthetic stock finished in black or green, and weighs 9.1875 lbs. The gun is equipped with forged carry handle and A2 front sight. It has a rifling twist of 1 in 8 inches and is set at 1 MOA. 

Armalite is an influential firearms manufacturer whose small arm designs have evolved into weapons currently in use today, like the M16 and M4, by militaries around the
 world. The company is currently based out of Geneseo, Illinois.

The only trades that I would be interested in is: a converted Saiga 12 gauge, a Wilson, Ed Brown or a Les Bauer .45. I CAN ADD CASH FOR THE RIGHT FIREARM.

Serial number in the 170,000 series.  Excellent condition, with original box including SN matched sticker.  Includes original magazine, second magazine of same era available for $30 extra.

These guns are based on the Walter Olympia, which in turn probably was based on the American Reising Target Pistol (with a fair number of modifications).

TWO Beautifully refinished stock Type 53 carbines Mosin Nagant. The Type 53 (T53) is identical to the Russian M44 with the attached folding bayonet. If you have never shot a Mosin carbine, you need to... It is a blast! I have three of these & also the longer model 91/30. A - after the first eotech was made scientists made clones, like with sheep.

Produced in Italy by Tanfoglio, the Appeal is a blowback-operated semi-automatic rimfire rifle—available in either .22 Long Rifle or.22 WMR ($18 more). The gun is unusual in that it is a bullpup, in which the breech and fire-control components lie behind the pistol grip and trigger.
